data.title: 17 fun facts for October, 15 (+3 bonus) - Historical events, discover what happened on this day.
data.meta_description: October 15 has been a day of significant events in history, from the birth of Queen Victoria's daughter Louise to the opening of the University of Chicago and the execution of Mata Hari. The day also marks notable landmarks in transportation, with the patenting of both the helicopter and the hovercraft, as well as the observance of various awareness days, including Global Handwashing Day and Pregnancy and Infant Loss Remembrance Day.
